! *** Required Parameters ***
type			= scalar
layer                   = n
function		= MAG ( KNTV (OBS) )
description		= Isotachs of observed wind ( knots ).  A couple of \
                        = \notes: to help focus on where convergence and the \
                        = \threat of heavy rain or precipitation could be, look \
                        = \at the nose of the 850mb and 950mb low-level jets \
                        = \in addition to where the wind barbs are convergent.\
                        = \If the nose of the low-level jet, maximum moisture transport, instability, and convergence \
                        = \all overlay, your risk of flooding rains has been increased greatly.
! *** End of Required Parameters ***
!
